  "base_commit": "91a1a1641a530ec65367cd405f8343c0c31a173f",
  "pr_number": 4426,
  "issue_number": 4423,
  "issue_title": "\ud83d\udc1b [Bug]: Logger middleware invokes ErrorHandler with MethodNotAllowed during fasthttp parser error recovery",
  "issue_body": "### Bug Description\n\nWhen fasthttp fails before normal Fiber routing, for example because request headers exceed ReadBufferSize, Fiber correctly maps fasthttp.ErrSmallBuffer to fiber.ErrRequestHeaderFieldsTooLarge.\n\nHowever, before calling the application ErrorHandler with that mapped parser error, Fiber's serverErrorHandler performs an internal middleware traversal with skipNonUseRoutes enabled.\n\nIf logger.New(...) middleware is installed, the logger runs during this internal traversal. The logger calls c.Next(); because normal routes are skipped, Fiber's router can reach its fallback method scan and return fiber.ErrMethodNotAllowed. The logger middleware then manually calls the application ErrorHandler with that chainErr.\n\nAs a result, the application ErrorHandler can be called with an unrelated MethodNotAllowed error before it is called with the real RequestHeaderFieldsTooLarge parser error.\n\nThis is surprising because the client sent only one request, and that request failed due to oversized headers before normal routing should happen.\n\nRelevant Fiber v3.3.0 flow:\n- app.serverErrorHandler maps fasthttp.ErrSmallBuffer to ErrRequestHeaderFieldsTooLarge.\n- app.serverErrorHandler sets skipNonUseRoutes and calls app.next.\n- logger middleware calls c.Next().\n- router fallback returns ErrMethodNotAllowed when another method has a matching route.\n- logger middleware manually calls app.ErrorHandler(c, chainErr).\n\n### How to Reproduce\n\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\n1. Create a Fiber app with a small ReadBufferSize.\n2. Add logger.New(...) middleware.\n3. Register a route for all methods, for example app.All(\"/\", handler).\n4. Send a PUT request to \"/\" with a header larger than ReadBufferSize.\n5. Observe that the application ErrorHandler is invoked with fiber.ErrMethodNotAllowed before/in addition to fiber.ErrRequestHeaderFieldsTooLarge.\n\n### Expected Behavior\n\nFor parser-level/server-level errors such as fasthttp.ErrSmallBuffer, the application ErrorHandler should only receive the mapped parser error, fiber.ErrRequestHeaderFieldsTooLarge.\n\nThe internal middleware traversal performed by serverErrorHandler should not cause logger middleware to invoke the application ErrorHandler with an unrelated routing error such as fiber.ErrMethodNotAllowed.\n\nPotential fix:\nWhen app.next/app.nextCustom is running with skipNonUseRoutes enabled, reaching the end of middleware traversal should not perform the normal 404/405 route fallback scan. It could return nil instead, because the traversal is only intended to run use-middleware during server error handling, not to resolve a route.\n\nFor example, before the NotFound/MethodNotAllowed fallback in router.go, Fiber could short-circuit when skipNonUseRoutes is true.\n\n### Fiber Version\n\nv3.3.0\n\n### Code Snippet (optional)\n\n```go\npackage main\n\nimport (\n\t\"errors\"\n\t\"io\"\n\t\"log\"\n\t\"net\"\n\t\"net/http\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/gofiber/fiber/v3\"\n\t\"github.com/gofiber/fiber/v3/middleware/logger\"\n)\n\nfunc main() {\n\tvar seen []error\n\n\tapp := fiber.New(fiber.Config{\n\t\tReadBufferSize: 512,\n\t\tErrorHandler: func(c fiber.Ctx, err error) error {\n\t\t\tlog.Printf(\"ErrorHandler got: %v\", err)\n\t\t\tseen = append(seen, err)\n\n\t\t\tif errors.Is(err, fiber.ErrRequestHeaderFieldsTooLarge) {\n\t\t\t\treturn c.SendStatus(fiber.StatusBadRequest)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\treturn fiber.DefaultErrorHandler(c, err)\n\t\t},\n\t})\n\n\tapp.Use(logger.New(logger.Config{\n\t\tStream: io.Discard,\n\t\tFormat: \"${status} ${method} ${path} ${error}\\n\",\n\t}))\n\n\tapp.Get(\"/\", func(c fiber.Ctx) error {\n\t\treturn c.SendString(\"ok\")\n\t})\n\n\tln, err := net.Listen(\"tcp\", \"127.0.0.1:0\")\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Fatal(err)\n\t}\n\n\tgo func() {\n\t\tif err := app.Listener(ln, fiber.ListenConfig{DisableStartupMessage: true}); err != nil {\n\t\t\tlog.Println(err)\n\t\t}\n\t}()\n\tdefer app.Shutdown()\n\n\treq, err := http.NewRequest(http.MethodPut, \"http://\"+ln.Addr().String()+\"/\", nil)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Fatal(err)\n\t}\n\treq.Header.Set(\"X-Large-Header\", strings.Repeat(\"x\", 2048))\n\n\tclient := &http.Client{Timeout: 5 * time.Second}\n\tresp, err := client.Do(req)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tlog.Fatal(err)\n\t}\n\tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n\n\tlog.Printf(\"response status: %d\", resp.StatusCode)\n\n\tfor i, err := range seen {\n\t\tlog.Printf(\"seen[%d]: %v\", i, err)\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n### Checklist:\n\n- [x] I agree to follow Fiber's [Code of Conduct](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/blob/main/.github/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md).\n- [x] I have checked for existing issues that describe my problem prior to opening this one.\n- [x] I understand that improperly formatted bug reports may be closed without explanation.",
